<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[r'=r-d(x,x'),]]></fr:tex>
then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B_{r'}(x')\subseteq  B_{r}(x)]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in  B_{r'}(x')]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d(y,x')<r']]></fr:tex>. Then the triangle inequality gives us
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[d(x,y)\leq  d(x,x')+d(x',y)<d(x,x')+r'=r.]]></fr:tex>
So <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in  B_{r}(x)]]></fr:tex>. Since <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in  B_{r'}(x')]]></fr:tex> was arbitrary, this then implies <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B_{r'}(x')\subseteq  B_{r}(x)]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><html:span
